      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STAR FURY (8) was sent out long odds last time but rocketed out of the boxes with a scorching early sectional and gave a sight before being swallowed up late, finishing a 5.5 lengths third (23.81) over 425m at Bendigo. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card last start despite being beaten. Sure to be about the mark. MY NAME'S EDEN (5) turned in a better effort at this track last start, finishing third behind Paw Estrella (24.05) in a Grade 4/5. Stalked the pace but found the line strongly. Expected to be in this for a long way. DR. ZAIDEN (2) is progressing well and looks close to another win after hitting the frame last run (24.00) at this track. Overdue and is among the main hopes. DR. WARREN (1) cannot be underestimated.",
